# CoinStack Coding Standards

## Tech Stack

- **Backend**: Python 3.12+, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy 2.0, Pydantic 2.x, SQLite
- **Frontend**: React 18, TypeScript 5.x, Vite, TanStack Query, Zustand, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui

## Python Standards

- Use type hints for all function parameters and returns
- Use Pydantic models for API schemas
- Use SQLAlchemy ORM models for database
- Follow PEP 8 naming conventions
- Keep functions under 50 lines when possible

## TypeScript Standards

- Use strict TypeScript (`strict: true`)
- Prefer interfaces over types for object shapes
- Use React functional components with hooks
- Keep components under 200 lines
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks

## File Organization

```
backend/
  app/
    models/      # SQLAlchemy models
    schemas/     # Pydantic schemas
    routers/     # FastAPI routers
    services/    # Business logic
    crud/        # Database operations

frontend/
  src/
    components/  # React components
    pages/       # Page components
    hooks/       # Custom hooks
    stores/      # Zustand stores
    types/       # TypeScript types
    lib/         # Utilities
```

## Commit Messages

- Use imperative mood: "Add feature" not "Added feature"
- Keep subject line under 72 characters
- Reference issues when applicable
